love the Taurus PT 92C Compact.Brief History of the Taurus PT92C Compact:Forjas Taurus in 1991 introduced its PT 92 Compact, better known as the PT 92C.  This was created by cutting down the standard PT 92's barrel and slide by one inch and reducing the magazine capacity from 15 rounds to 13 and shortening the grip to match.  Compared to the full-sized models the PT 92C lost three ounces, weighing 31 ounces without ammunition.  To compete with the Beretta's 8-shot Type M variant.  Despite its excellent performance, Forjas Taurus stopped production of the PT 92C in 1996.Were service guns in the Brazilian Air Force.  Taurus bought the Beretta plant in Sao Paulo when their contract with the Brazilian government ended.The only major difference on the Taurus from the Beretta is the placement of
